OL,3,CHealth body writes to parents after
OL,4,CHepatitis A outbreak in Welsh town
OL,6,FPublic Health Wales (PHW) is urging
OL,7,Fpeople to wash their hands following
OL,8,Fan outbreak of Hepatitis A in Barry.
OL,10,FPHW has written to parents and carers
OL,11,Fwho have children in primary schools
OL,12,Fin the town to ask them to ensure that
OL,13,Fthey and their children are extra
OL,14,Fcareful with handwashing.
OL,16,FHepatitis A is a viral infection that
OL,17,Faffects the liver that, in most cases,
OL,18,Fis a mild illness that most people
OL,19,Fmake a full recovery from without long
OL,20,Fterm health problems.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/5
